   <conbody>
      <p class="- topic/p ">Checking out files and attachments that are in Salesforce ensures that you are working on the most recent version of the file.</p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">You can check-out files that are saved in Chatter &gt; Files or those that are in the Notes and Attachments section of objects, such as Opportunities or Accounts. Multiple people can check-out the same file at the same time and subsequently check-in new separate versions. So to ensure each version of a document has the expected content in it, your organization should set up guidelines around document sharing. </p>
      <p class="- topic/p ">Whether you have access to files in Chatter or in Notes and Attachments is controlled by standard Salesforce file sharing settings and Standard Salesforce access rights to objects. There is no restriction on the number of files you can check-out. If there is an issue with documents while you are working on them, standard Microsoft Office backup and recovery functionality is used.</p>
